<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Oil System Module Assembly and Secondary
        Filtration - Cleaning and Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Cleaning the Oil System Module</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, the oil cooler must be replaced if there was a bearing failure. Debris
                        from a bearing failure cannot be removed from the oil cooler.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not attempt to clean the assembled oil system module in solvent.
                        Solvent will be trapped in the oil cooler, regulator valve assembly, and oil thermal valve
                        assembly. Failure to follow this caution could result in engine damage.
                    </para>
                    <para>The following items should be removed:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Oil cooler</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Regulator valve assembly</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Oil thermal valve assembly</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                    <para>The oil system module housing and lube adapter can be cleaned in solvent and blown dry with
                        clean filtered
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Immerse the disassembled oil cooler housing and lube adapter into a suitable solvent.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Flush and drain the oil cooler housing and lube adapter to remove any residue. Dry all
                    components with filtered
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the oil cooler housing for blocked orifices and damaged threads. Replace oil
                    cooler housing if required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove any debris that may be blocking the filter bypass valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil supply fitting (M18) on top of oil filter header and discard
                    O-ring seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651008.2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH13/H13031.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Oil supply tube fitting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Direction of oil flow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply wire mesh screen</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect screen for damage or particle obstruction. Clean or replace oil supply tube
                    fitting screen as necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring onto fitting and thread into oil filter header. Tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_219.xml" xrefid="t2651002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
